"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The roc_curve function is not designed to handle multiclass classification problems directly. In this case, the code is trying to calculate the ROC curve for each class separately, but it's passing the entire y_test array to the roc_curve function, which is incorrect. The correct approach is to binarize the output for each class using the y_onehot_test array.\",\n  \"patch\": \"28,29c28,29\\n< for i in range(n_classes):\\n<     fpr[i], tpr[i], thresh = roc_curve(y_test, y_score, pos_label=i)\\n---\\n> for i in range(n_classes):\\n>     fpr[i], tpr[i], thresh = roc_curve(y_onehot_test[:, i], y_score[:, i])\\n\"\n}"